  "excerpt": "If you’re in Los Angeles and need an emergency dentist, don’t panic.  There’s an option that’s perfect for your situation.",
  "content": "<div class=\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\">\n        <h2>Overview</h2>\n<p>If you’re in Los Angeles and need an emergency dentist, don’t panic. There’s an option that’s perfect for your situation. For Los Angeles emergency dental care, there’s no better choice than Exquisite Dentistry. A dental emergency can strike at any time, but it’s especially troublesome when you’re far from home and you need a dentist. If you’ve been in the situation before, you understand the helpless feeling. You don’t know whether to wait until you get home to see your regular dentist or try to find someone to help you immediately. If you decide to search for a dentist, it can be overwhelming to sort through the dozens of practices finding just the right dentist to help.</p>\n<h2>A Comforting Environment</h2>\n<p>When you need to see an emergency dentist in Los Angeles, Dr. Alexie Aguil is the only dentist you want to see. His office at Exquisite Dental can quickly help your dental issues all while providing a calm and peaceful environment to allow you to relax. When you’re traveling and have to see a different dentist, it can add pressure to an already stressful situation. That’s why Exquisite Dentistry is different from other emergency dentists in Los Angeles. You’ll realize how distinct our office is as soon as you walk through the door, with amenities such as: Calming essential oils: Our spa-like atmosphere will immediately calm you as you smell the relaxing scent of essential oils diffusing throughout the office. Low lighting: Instead of the harsh lighting traditionally found in dentist offices that heightens your anxiety, soft lights will help soothe your nerves and allow your tension to ease. Noise-canceling headphones: The noises of a dentist office can be off-putting to some patients. To relieve this issue, you’ll receive a pair of noise-canceling headphones before you begin treatment. You can watch your favorite Netflix show or movie on our TV’s without hearing a thing. Warm blankets and neck pillows: The ultimate in relaxation, you’ll feel comfortable ensconced by the warmth of our plush blankets. A soft neck pillow will also help your anxiety fade away. As you can see, if you need to see an emergency dentist in Los Angeles, Exquisite Dentistry is unlike any other office you can find. Instead of a trip to the dentist ruining your trip, you’ll find that a visit to Exquisite Dentistry will actually rejuvenate you for the remainder of your time in the City of Angels.</p>\n<h2>Restore Your Smile’s Brilliance</h2>\n<p>With your smile the best it’s ever looked, your confidence will be at an all-time high</p>\n<h3>CONTACT EXQUISITE DENTISTRY</h3>\n<p>(323) 272-2388 Call to schedule your cosmetic dentist appointment and experience true luxury.</p>\n<h3>Knowledgeable Emergency Care</h3>\n<p>Of course, a comfortable office is not the only consideration you have when looking for emergency dental care in Los Angeles. You’ll want to see a dentist who can quickly, efficiently, and painlessly ease your acute symptoms. How do you know if you’re experiencing a “dental emergency?” In general, any dental problem that requires some type of treatment to save a tooth, stop ongoing tissue bleeding, or alleviate severe pain and discomfort should be considered to be a dental emergency. Some common dental problems that can necessitate an emergency dentist visit in Los Angeles include:</p>\n<h3>Toothache</h3>\n<p>Broken, cracked, chipped tooth Knocked out tooth Loose tooth Tooth out of alignment Injury to the inside of the mouth Severe infection or abscess Exquisite Dentistry uses the latest technology to ensure you receive the best possible outcome from your visit. We also offer pain-free sedation dentistry, giving you an additional option for further comfort and relaxation.</p>\n<h2>Don’t Let Your Situation Worsen</h2>\n<p>You may believe that you can wait to see your dentist when you return home from your trip to Los Angeles, but that’s probably not a wise choice. It’s important to keep in mind that seeing an emergency dentist while visiting Los Angeles can mean the difference between saving or losing a tooth. If you’re visiting Los Angeles and need emergency dental care, you’ll need to find a dentist that’s close by and leaves openings in his or her schedule to accommodate dental emergencies. Seeing an emergency dentist while visiting Los Angeles can not only mean the difference between saving and losing a tooth, but it can also mean the difference between saving and ruining your trip. Exquisite Dentistry should be at the top of your list, not only because of our relaxing office and expert care, but because we always make time for Los Angeles visitors with dental emergencies. Located right in the heart of West Hollywood, Dr. Aguil and team can take care of all your emergency general dentistry needs, as well as restorative procedures such as root canals, crowns, and dental implants.</p>\n<h3>Exquisite Dentistry, a</h3>\n<p>general and cosmetic dentistry practice, is considered to be one of the top practices in Southern California when it comes to patient care and comfort. The goal is to make every appointment as convenient and pain-free as possible. If you’re in a situation where you need an emergency dentist visit in Los Angeles, we’ll provide you with the most up-to-date dental procedures and try to make you feel as comfortable as you would if you were at your own dentist. That’s our promise to you.</p>\n<h2>Contact Us Today For An Appointment</h2>\n<p>Whether you’re visiting L.A. with family or on a business trip and are faced with some sort of dental emergency, you need the services of a dentist that takes emergency appointments. Remember – getting to see a dentist can help minimize or prevent any potential damage to your tooth as well as the nerves, tissues, bones, and blood vessels in your mouth. Contact our office to schedule your emergency dentist visit in Los Angeles with one of the top dentists in all of L.A., Dr. Alexie Aguil at Exquisite Dentistry. We’ve been caring for our patients’ oral health since 2006, and we’d love to help you too. Call us today to help with your dental emergency!</p>\n      </div>",
